From: bluecat <lmhtq1991@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 29 May 2026 13:25:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Phase C-6 L39/L40: cap-aware constant-pool-cache index + cap-aware lea

Bytecode templates execute and now reach constant-pool resolution. Two
mechanical cap-arithmetic fixes, the second high-leverage:

  L39 get_cache_and_index_at_bcp: `add(cache, rcpool, index, LSL 5)` is
      an integer add that strips the ConstantPoolCache capability tag, so
      the subsequent ldar/[cache] faults. New cap_add_reg helper (Morello
      `add Cd,Cn,Xm,uxtx` = 0xC2A06000|..., verified vs clang); pre-shift
      the index with lsl then cap-add.

  L40 Address::lea (base_plus_offset and base_plus_offset_reg): the
      generic lea emitted integer add/sub, stripping the base capability
      on EVERY lea(reg, Address(cap_base, ...)). Made it cap-aware:
      cap_add_imm/cap_sub_imm for small offsets, mov+cap_add_reg for
      large, cap_add_reg (with optional pre-shift) for the index form.
      This is high-leverage — it fixes address computation across many
      bytecode templates at once (the +0x50 cpcache header offset that
      faulted right after L39, and others).

New helpers in macroAssembler_aarch64.hpp: cap_add_reg, cap_add_imm.

RESULT: getstatic/resolve templates run; execution crosses into the
libjvm.so constant-pool resolution runtime. Next fault (L41):
frame::interpreter_frame_method() (C++ frame walking) reads a Method*
from the interpreter frame — a frame-layout / cap-tag consistency issue
between the interpreter's cap-STP frame stores and the C++ frame reader.

Session: 39 commits, 101 build iterations, L25-L40 resolved.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

